author: Joe Flint
title: NBC Struggles to Build Up Pipeline of New Shows
text:
Comcast Corp.’s NBC would appear to be in pole position as the new TV season gets under way this week. The network has two huge programs, “Sunday Night Football” and “The Voice,” and for the past two years has topped the ratings in the coveted audience of 18- to 49-year-olds.
But underneath the hood of that fast-looking car is an engine that needs a tuneup.
